article.headline: South Alabama 91, Arkansas State 78
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Ernest Little scored 20 points and Leandro Buboltz added 19 to lead South Alabama to a 91-78 Sun Belt Conference win over Arkansas State on Thursday. It was the first conference loss of the season for Arkansas State (7-8 overall, 2-1). Little led South Alabama (7-6, 1-1) with eight boards. Demetric Bennett also scored 16 points for the Jaquars and Daon Merritt added 13. Isaac Wells led the Indians with 20 points and 12 rebounds. Adrian Banks added 19 points, hitting 5 of 9 from the three-point arc. Ryan Wedel added 10 more points. South Alabama build a quick 16-8 lead, hitting six straight threes, mostly from Buboltz. The Jaguars expanded the gap by as much as 14 before the Indians fought back and twice cut the margin to six. South Alabama was up 48-38 at the half after Merritt hit a layup with three seconds remaining. Arkansas State managed to get the point difference into single digits in the second half, but never took the lead. The Jaguars outrebounded the Indians 36-31.
